Amazon FSx makes it easy and cost effective to launch, run, and scale feature-rich, high-performance file systems in the cloud. 
It supports a wide range of workloads with its reliability, security, scalability, and broad set of capabilities. 
Amazon FSx is built on the latest AWS compute, networking, and disk technologies to provide high performance and lower TCO. 
And as a fully managed service, it handles hardware provisioning, patching, and backups -- freeing you up to focus on your applications, your end users, and your business.



Amazon FSx file systems:
-----------------------

1. Amazon FSx for NetApp ONTAP
Amazon FSx for NetApp ONTAP
Fully managed shared storage built on NetApp’s popular ONTAP file system.


2. Amazon FSx for OpenZFS
Amazon FSx for OpenZFS
Fully managed shared storage built on the popular OpenZFS file system.


3. Amazon FSx for Windows File Server
Amazon FSx for Windows File Server
Fully managed shared storage built on Windows Server.


4. Amazon FSx for Lustre
Amazon FSx for Lustre
Fully managed shared storage built on the world’s most popular high-performance file system.

